definition.value: A department of El Salvador in the eastern part of the country. The capital is San Miguel.
A department of El Salvador in the center of the country. The capital is San Vicente.
A department of El Salvador. Located in the northeast part of the country, its capital is San Francisco Gotera.
A department of El Salvador in the west of the country. The capital is Ahuachapan. In the South it has the Apenca-Ilamatepec Range and the Cerro Grande de Apaneca (Apaneca Grand Hill).
A department of El Salvador in the west central part of the country. The capital is San Salvador, which is also the national capital.
A department of El Salvador in the western part of the country. The capital is Sonsonate.
A department of El Salvador in the south central area of the country. The capital is Zacatecoluca.
A department of El Salvador in the north central part of the country. The capital is Sensuntepeque.
A department of El Salvador. It is located in the eastern part of the country and its capital is La Union.
A department of El Salvador in the northwest of the country. The capital is Santa Ana.
A department of El Salvador, located in the southwest of the country. The capital is Santa Tecla.
A department of El Salvador, located in the center of the country.
A department of El Salvador in the southeast of the country (Lenca region). The capital is Usulutan.
One of the 18 departments (departamentos) into which the Central American nation of Honduras is divided. The departmental capital is Puerto Lempira.
One of the departments in the western part of Honduras. The departmental capital is the town of Santa Rosa de Copan.
One of the 18 departments into which the Central American nation of Honduras is divided.
One of the 18 departments of Honduras Central America, located in the western part of the country with borders with El Salvador. The departmental capital is Gracias.
One of the 18 departments into which the Central American nation of Honduras is divided. The departmental capital is the city of La Paz.
One of the departments of Honduras. It is located in the central part of the nation. The departmental capital is Tegucigalpa.
One of the 18 departments (departamentos) into which the Central American nation of Honduras is divided. The departmental capital is Comayagua.
A department in Honduras. The departmental capital is the town of La Esperanza.
One of the 18 departments into which the Central American nation of Honduras is divided. It was created in 1881. The departmental capital is Trujillo.
One of the 18 departments into which the Central American nation of Honduras is divided. The departmental capital is Juticalpa.
One of the 18 departments into which the Central American nation of Honduras is divided. The departmental capital is Yoro.
One of the 18 departments into which the Central American nation of Honduras is divided. The departmental capital is Nacaome. The department faces the Gulf of Fonseca.
One of the 18 departments (departamentos) into which the Central American nation of Honduras is divided. The departmental capital is Santa Barbara.
One of the 18 departments of Honduras, Central America, located in the West and bordering both El Salvador and Guatemala. It was formed in 1906 from part of Copan department.

A province of Kazakhstan. It occupies the easternmost part of Kazakhstan, along both sides of the Irtysh River and Lake Zaysan. Its capital is Oskemen (also referred to as Ust-Kamenogorsk). The province borders Russia in the north and northeast and the People's Republic of China (Xinjiang Uighur Autonomous Region) in the south and southeast.

A province of Kazakhstan. Its capital is Aktau. It has much of Kazakhstan's Caspian Shore. It also borders neighboring countries Turkmenistan and Uzbekistan. Mangystau also borders two other Kazakh provinces: Aktobe Province and Atyrau Province.
A province of Kazakhstan. Its capital is Karagandy.
A province in Kazakhstan.

One of the 26 regions of Tanzania. Kibaha serves as the region's capital. The region is bordered to the North by the Tanga Region, to the East by Dar-es-Salaam and the Indian Ocean, to the South by the Lindi Region and to the West by the Morogoro Region.
One of the regions of Tanzania. The capital of the region is the city of Dodoma.
One of Tanzania's 26 administrative regions. The regional capital is Iringa.
One of Tanzania's 26 administrative regions. The regional capital is Bukoba. The region neighbors Uganda, Rwanda and Burundi and lies across Lake Victoria from Kenya.

One of Tanzania's 26 administrative regions. The regional capital is Kigoma. It is bordered to the North by the Kagera Region, to the East by the Shinyanga and Tabora Regions, to the South by the Rukwa Region, to the West by Lake Tanganyika which forms a border with the Democratic Republic of the Congo and to the Northwest by Burundi.
One of the 26 regions in Tanzania. The capital of the region is Moshi.

One of Tanzania's 26 administrative regions. The regional capital is Lindi. The Lindi region borders on Pwani, Morogoro, Ruvuma, and Mtwara. Much of the western part of the region is in the Selous Game Reserve.

One of the 26 Regions of Tanzania. Babati serves as the Region's capital. It is bordered to the North by the Arusha Region, to the Northeast by the Kilimanjaro Region, to the East by the Tanga Region, to the South by the Dodoma Region, to the Southwest by the Singida Region and to the Northwest by the Shinyanga Region.

One of the 26 regions of Tanzania. The region is named after the Mara River. Musoma serves as the Region's capital. The neighbouring regions are Mwanza and Shinyanga(to the south), Arusha (to the south east)and Kagera (through Lake Victoria). To the north east, it borders the Republic of Kenya.

One of Tanzania's 26 administrative regions. The regional capital is Mbeya. It is bordered to the northwest by Tabora Region, to the northeast by Singida Region, to the East by Iringa Region, to the South by Zambia and Malawi and to the West by Rukwa Region.

One of the regions of Tanzania. The boundary with Mozambique to the south is formed by the Ruvuma River. To the west, the Mtwara Region is bordered by the Ruvuma Region, to the North, by the Lindi Region, and to the East the region is bordered by the Indian Ocean.
